dashboard.definition:
{
	"title": "Convert license.log into metrics events",
	"description": "",
	"inputs": {
		"input_time": {
			"type": "input.timerange",
			"title": "",
			"options": {
				"defaultValue": "@w0,now",
				"token": "time"
			}
		},
		"input_splitby": {
			"type": "input.dropdown",
			"title": "Select splitby",
			"options": {
				"defaultValue": "sourcetype",
				"items": [
					{
						"label": "host",
						"value": "host"
					},
					{
						"label": "source",
						"value": "source"
					},
					{
						"label": "sourcetype",
						"value": "sourcetype"
					},
					{
						"label": "index",
						"value": "into_index"
					},
					{
						"label": "splunk_server",
						"value": "on_indexer"
					},
					{
						"label": "pool",
						"value": "allocated_to_pool"
					}
				],
				"token": "selected_splitby"
			}
		},
		"input_span": {
			"type": "input.text",
			"title": "Span (seconds)",
			"options": {
				"defaultValue": "60",
				"prefix": "span=",
				"suffix": "sec",
				"token": "selected_span_min_30_secs"
			}
		},
		"input_limit": {
			"type": "input.text",
			"title": "Limit for split by",
			"options": {
				"defaultValue": "20",
				"token": "selected_limit"
			}
		}
	},
	"defaults": {
		"dataSources": {
			"ds.search": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {}
				}
			},
			"ds.spl2": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {}
				}
			}
		},
		"visualizations": {
			"global": {
				"showProgressBar": true
			}
		}
	},
	"visualizations": {
		"viz_markdown": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "# Problem description\n\nRunning searches to compute license usgae is very expensive as license.log is held as _raw strings. We must fully parse each log line to access the value for bytes \"b\" and extract the values for host, sourcetype, instance extra at point of search. This makes it difficult to do deep history analysis on license usage.\n\n## Existing Solutions\nPrimarily you must search the license log file with `_raw` search and wait\n\n## Proposed Solution\nWe will copy the events from license_usage.log so that they are also stored in the `_metrics` index so that they can be processed using the `mstats` command.\n\n###  Example log line\n\n    09-18-2020 10:02:11.793 +0100 INFO  LicenseUsage - type=Usage s=\"my_host\" st=\"m_sourcetype\" h=\"my_host\" o=\"\" idx=\"default\" i=\"18F9C3EA-EBB2-497C-801A-098D0C52F9E2\" pool=\"auto_generated_pool_enterprise\" b=2034451 poolsz=53687091200\n\n* `s` : the source that used license\n* `st` : the sourcetype that used license\n* `h` : the host that used license\n* `i` : the GUID of the indexer that reported the license_usgae\n* `idx` : the index the data was written to\n* `pool` : the name of the license pool\n* `b` : the number of bytes written for the `source`, `host` and `sourcetype` on the `indexer` into the `index`\n* `poolz` : the total pool_size\n\n#### Back filling data\n\nTo back fill your existing data into `_metrics` you use `oneshot` to reload the data and target the `metricify_license` sourcetype\n\n    /Applications/Splunk/bin/splunk nom on -auth admin:password /Applications/Splunk/var/log/splunk/license_usage.log  -sourcetype metricify_license -index main\n\n\n### The steps performed to process data\n\n1. We intercept the events created by the license_usage.log file using a source specific stanza\n1. We use a transform that calls CLONE_SOURCETYPE to create a new event with a new sourcetype `metricify_license`\n1. We let the orignal event countinue to indexed as per normal and be written to `the _internal` index\n1. We intercept the cloned event by its sourcetype `metricify_license` \n1. We then process the cloned event with a `REGEX` transform and to turn it into a metrics compliant event\n    1. We assign a fixed value to `metric_name` and copy extract value for \"b\" and copy it into `_value` \n    1. We extract the other fields assigning them to more descriptive indexed fields names - these become dimensions\n1. We route all other types other than \"usage\n1. We copy the indexed fields for host, source and sourcetype in to the proper metrics fields\n1. Finally we assign the `index` field to `_metrics` steering the event into the metrics index\n"
			}
		},
		"viz_mstats": {
			"type": "splunk.column",
			"dataSources": {
				"primary": "ds_mstats"
			},
			"options": {
				"stackMode": "stacked",
				"legendTruncation": "ellipsisMiddle"
			},
			"showProgressBar": true,
			"title": "This chart is calculated by mstats"
		},
		"viz_raw": {
			"type": "splunk.column",
			"dataSources": {
				"primary": "ds_raw"
			},
			"options": {
				"stackMode": "stacked",
				"legendTruncation": "ellipsisMiddle"
			},
			"showProgressBar": true,
			"title": "This chart is calculated via raw search"
		},
		"viz_conf_props": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "### props.conf\n\nFrom `default/props.conf` \u2014 verbatim:\n\n```ini\n# Convert the cloned license_usage event into a metrics-compliant event and\n# route it into the _metrics index.\n[metricify_license]\nTRANSFORMS-clone_and_convert = metricify_license-extract_fields, shared-drop_useless_time_fields, metricify_license-reassign_meta_fields_and_route_to_index\n```\n"
			}
		},
		"viz_conf_transforms": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "### transforms.conf\n\nFrom `default/transforms.conf` \u2014 verbatim:\n\n```ini\n# Clone each license_usage.log event onto a new sourcetype so the clone can\n# be parsed as metrics. The original is still written to _internal as normal.\n[metricify_license-clone]\nREGEX = .\nCLONE_SOURCETYPE = metricify_license\nFORMAT = $0\nDEST_KEY = _raw\n\n# Lift every field out of the license_usage log line. `b` becomes _value\n# (the metric value), the rest become dimensions. The metric name is\n# hard-coded to \"license_usage\". Each field has two mutually exclusive\n# capture groups (quoted and unquoted) and both flow into the same target.\n[metricify_license-extract_fields]\nSOURCE_KEY = _raw\nREGEX = type=(\\S+)\\ss=(?:\"([^\"]*)\"|(\\S*))\\s+st=(?:\"([^\"]+)\"|(\\S+))\\s+h=(?:\"([^\"]+)\"|(\\S+))\\so=\"[^\"]*\"\\sidx=(?:\"([^\"]+)\"|(\\S+))\\si=\"([^\"]+)\"\\spool=\"([^\"]+)\"\\sb=(\\d+)\\spoolsz=(\\d+)\nFORMAT = metric_name::\"license_usage\" type::\"$1\" from_source::\"$2$3\" from_sourcetype::\"$4$5\" from_host::\"$6$7\" into_index::\"$8$9\" on_indexer::\"$10\" allocated_to_pool::\"$11\" _value::\"$12\" pool_size::\"$13\"\nWRITE_META = true\n\n# Keep only type=Usage rows, move from_* into the real host/sourcetype/source\n# slots, drop the intermediates, and route the result into the _metrics index.\n[metricify_license-reassign_meta_fields_and_route_to_index]\nINGEST_EVAL = queue=if(type=\"Usage\", queue, \"nullQueue\"), host=from_host, sourcetype=from_sourcetype, source=from_source,  type:=null(), from_host:=null(), from_sourcetype:=null(), from_source:=null(), index:=\"_metrics\"\n```\n"
			}
		}
	},
	"dataSources": {
		"ds_mstats": {
			"name": "mstats chart",
			"type": "ds.search",
			"options": {
				"query": "| mstats sum(_value) as bytes_indexed $selected_span_min_30_secs$ where index=_metrics metric_name=license_usage  by $selected_splitby$\n| xyseries _time $selected_splitby$ bytes_indexed\n| head $selected_limit$",
				"queryParameters": {
					"earliest": "$time.earliest$",
					"latest": "$time.latest$"
				}
			}
		},
		"ds_raw": {
			"name": "Raw search chart",
			"type": "ds.search",
			"options": {
				"query": "index=_internal TERM(LicenseUsage) sourcetype=splunkd NOT(IndexProcessor) TERM(type=Usage)\n| eval splitby=case(\"$selected_splitby$\"=\"host\", h, \"$selected_splitby$\"=\"source\", s, \"$selected_splitby$\"=\"sourcetype\", st, \"$selected_splitby$\"=\"into_index\", idx, \"$selected_splitby$\"=\"on_indexer\", i, \"$selected_splitby$\"=\"allocated_to_pool\", pool)\n| timechart limit=$selected_limit$ $selected_span_min_30_secs$ sum(b) as license_used by splitby",
				"queryParameters": {
					"earliest": "$time.earliest$",
					"latest": "$time.latest$"
				}
			}
		}
	},
	"layout": {
		"globalInputs": [
			"input_time",
			"input_splitby",
			"input_span",
			"input_limit"
		],
		"layoutDefinitions": {
			"layout_1": {
				"type": "grid",
				"options": {
					"width": 1440,
					"height": 250
				},
				"structure": [
					{
						"item": "viz_markdown",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 0,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 1200
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_mstats",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 0,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 600
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_raw",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 600,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 600
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_conf_props",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 1200,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 480
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_conf_transforms",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 1200,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 480
						}
					}
				]
			}
		},
		"options": {
			"submitButton": false
		},
		"tabs": {
			"items": [
				{
					"label": "New tab",
					"layoutId": "layout_1"
				}
			]
		}
	},
	"applicationProperties": {
		"hideEdit": false,
		"hideExport": false
	}
}
